          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>The Hague</placeName>, <date>August
                                                  1, 1853</date>.</p>
                              <p>To the Reverend</p>
                              <p>Sir <addressee>I. Leeser</addressee>,</p>
                              <p>at <placeName>P<hi rend="underline"
                                        >hila</hi>delphia</placeName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Some months ago I had the<lb/> honour to forward
                                        to you some<lb/> literary productions in answer to<lb/> your
                                        very cheering letter I did receive<lb/> some times before. I
                                        hope the<lb/> said publications have been duly received<lb/>
                                        by you.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">These few lines are destined<lb/> to recommend to
                                        your benevolent<lb/> attention <persName>M. B. D'Ancona de
                                                  Sear<add>?</add></persName>,<lb/> Dutchman, of a
                                        very respectable family,<lb/> and an
                                                  <sic>irreprocheable</sic> character, himself,<lb/>
                                        who, by revertes of fortune, has been<lb/> driven to the new
                                        world, <add>?</add> the research<lb/> for him and his
                                        numerous family of the<lb/> necessary means of
                                        existence.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Will be so kind to lend him the<lb/> support you
                                        may dispose of: <persName>M. d'Ancona</persName><lb/>
                                        deserves it, by his conduct and relations.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Believe me, Sir, truly your</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">most humble servant, <persName role="author">J H
                                                  Belinfante</persName></p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">To</p>
                              <p>the <addressee>Reverend Sir I. Leeser</addressee>,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Jewish minister</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">at</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="Envelope"/>
                              <p><hi rend="underline">Rev</hi>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
